<headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 27 at 2:07PM MDT  by NWS Pocatello</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of southwestern Cassia
County through 245 PM MDT...
At 206 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 15
miles southeast of Rogerson, or 19 miles northeast of Jackpot, moving
east at 20 mph.
HAZARD...Nickel size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.
Locations impacted include...
Bostetter Ranger Station.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.88 IN
MAX WIND GUST...&lt;30 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
